  "prompt": "How can I get a job in Infosys off campus?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to get a job at Infosys off-campus:\n\n1. Online Application Process\n- Visit Infosys careers website\n- Create a profile\n- Upload your resume\n- Search and apply for relevant job openings\n\n2. Preparation\n- Improve technical skills\n- Practice coding and problem-solving\n- Learn programming languages like Java, Python\n- Prepare for technical and HR interviews\n\n3. Eligibility Criteria\n- BE/B.Tech/MCA/M.Sc degree\n- Minimum 60% marks in academics\n- No active backlogs\n- Good communication skills\n\n4. Networking\n- Attend Infosys recruitment drives\n- Connect with Infosys employees on LinkedIn\n- Participate in tech conferences and events\n\n5. Skill Enhancement\n- Get relevant certifications\n- Build a strong portfolio\n- Learn emerging technologies\n- Develop soft skills\n\n6. Referral\n- Ask friends/contacts working in Infosys\n- Employee referrals can increase chances\n\n7. Online Platforms\n- Apply through job portals\n- Check Infosys recruitment websites\n- Monitor company's career page regularly\n\n8. Competitive Exams\n- Consider appearing for Infosys national-level recruitment tests\n\nPersistence and continuous skill development are key to securing an off-campus job.",
